    {
        "content": "<p>I cannot find in this thread an answer to <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110087\">@Kim Morrison</span> 's question about \"how is one meant to handle this\". Is there any advance? For instance, in</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib.GroupTheory.Subgroup.Center</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Monoid</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bool</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">mul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bool.and</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">mul_assoc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">z</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bool.and_assoc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">..</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">one</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">one_mul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bool.true_and</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">mul_one</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bool.and_true</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>in the second field (<code>mul_assoc</code>) after the three <code>intro</code> I would like to change <code>*</code> to <code>&amp;</code> so that I can realize what lemma to apply (of course in this mwe things are too easy, but if the first field <code>mul</code> was \"difficult\" it can be handy to be able to \"unfold\" it).</p>",
